## 📁 DOCUMENTATION STRUCTURE DISCIPLINE

**JANGAN bikin dokumen sembarangan.** Sebelum create/update dokumen:

### Allowed Folders (sesuai Lakasir structure):
```
docs/                  ← Project docs (organized by domain/feature)
  ├── api/             ← API docs
  ├── features/        ← Feature specs
  ├── planning/        ← Planning & roadmap
  └── [etc per domain]

.github/instructions/  ← GitHub/PR instruction summaries ONLY
.cursor/               ← Cursor rules (.mdc files) ONLY
README.md              ← Top-level reference
AGENTS.md              ← Agent rules (already exists)
AUDIT_REPORT.md        ← Audit findings
QUICK_FIXES.md         ← Quick fix guide
```

### Naming Consistency:
- `.cursor/` → `kebab-case.mdc` (00-session-preamble.mdc, 01-task-rules.mdc)
- `docs/` → `UPPERCASE-or-README.md` (IMPLEMENTATION.md, README.md, etc)
- `docs/api/` → `resource-name.md` (products.md, users.md, transactions.md)
- Root `.md` → DESCRIPTIVE-NAME.md (AUDIT_REPORT.md, QUICK_FIXES.md)

### BEFORE Creating Dokumen:
- [ ] Folder already exists? Use it. Don't create new folder.
- [ ] Dokumen sudah ada? Don't duplicate. Link or update instead.
- [ ] File naming sesuai rule? (kebab-case, UPPERCASE, extension)
- [ ] File ini akan tracked di git atau local-only?
- [ ] File ini ter-reference di index/README atau orphan?

### NOT ALLOWED:
- ❌ Random `.md` di root (cek AGENTS.md dulu)
- ❌ Create subfolder baru tanpa alasan
- ❌ Duplicate docs di multiple places
- ❌ Orphan files (unreferenced, untracked, ignored)
- ❌ Inconsistent naming (UPPERCASE vs lowercase mix)

